Sentencas: ZnO/NiO nanocomposite electrodes have successfully been developed using a cost-effective method, and for the first time used in LT-SOFCs at 300-600 degrees C.
Titulo: ZnO/NiO nanocomposite electrodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: They exhibit high conductivity and a dual catalytic functionality in both the cathode and the anode for the electrochemical reduction of O-2 and oxidation of H-2, respectively.
Titulo: ZnO/NiO nanocomposite electrodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An excellent fuel cell performance, e.g. a maximum power density of 1107 W cm(-2), has been shown for a symmetrical fuel cell that contained ZnO/NiO nanocomposite electrodes at 500 degrees C. To our knowledge, to date this is by far the highest power density achieved at this temperature.
Titulo: ZnO/NiO nanocomposite electrodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
